# W.O.L.K. Core Standards

- Use `yarn`, not `npm`.
- Do not add CI, workflows, or automation scaffolding unless explicitly requested.
- Keep runtime-visible branding centralized in `src/shared/branding.ts` when touching app names, links, or public-facing labels.
- Prefer typed preload APIs over generic IPC escape hatches. Do not expose catch-all channel listeners from `preload.ts`.
- Do not add startup permission prompts unless the feature genuinely requires them and the app flow makes that clear.
- After substantive changes, run `yarn test`.
- If a change affects release-facing behavior, keep `README.md`, legal files, and release docs aligned with the code.
